       <br />

        <h2>Do you think that you will ever give up loving horses?   I like horses too, they’re very beautiful creatures.  When did you start liking horses?</h2>

        <p>I´m happy to hear that there are many horse lovers out there! I loved horses for as long as I can remember and I know I always will. I started riding when I was 3-years-old. Keep loving horses!</p>


        <h2>Do you have any tips on helping me to convince my parents to get me a horse?</h2>

        <p>I sorry but I can´t help you to convince your parents to get you a horse.
My mom also rode and we had our own little farm, so we were able to board horses at home. The best advice I can give is that if you really want a horse, keep up with the sport and enjoy the horses as much as you can. It´s a very expensive hobby so maybe your parents need to see that you want to ride as a long-term goal, not just a passing fancy. Please do remember: Getting you own horse does not make you happy, it´s being with horses that makes you happy!</p>

        
        <h2>I have jumped 60cm with a horse named Pinky.  But, he is a bit worried.  Do you have any tips?</h2>

        <p>How much have you have jumped Pinky? Sometimes if horse and rider are new to each other, the horse will get nervous. Not because he does not want to do it, but because it doesn’t feel “natural.”</p>

        <p>Try to start up with smaller jumps, only 30 to 40cm, think a lot about what you do while jumping; are you giving him the right help at the right time? Are your reins too loose and are your legs supporting him both before and after the jump? Are the distances between jumps right? Are the jumps standing without any support? If they are, try to move them closer to the barrier, so you have support on one side. If you use these right, you will make it more fun and make both yourself and Pinky better at jumping.</p>
		
        <p>Remember that when professional riders are training with their horses they mostly practice at lower jumps because when they do, they make the Tekniker better.</p>

